The National Department of Health (NDoH) has reported 972 new COVID-19 cases from a total of 17 697 tests conducted in the last 24 hours, which represents a 5.5% positivity rate. The NDoH says that due to the ongoing audit exercise there may be a backlog of COVID-19 mortality cases reported. The department has also reported 13 deaths, of which none occurred in the past 24 to 48 hours. There are now a total of 99 725 COVID-19 related deaths in South Africa since March 2020. Provincial breakdown The majority of new cases on Sunday are from Gauteng (37%), followed by Western Cape (25%). KwaZulu-Natal accounted for 17%; Free State, Mpumalanga and North West each accounted for 5% respectively; Northern Cape accounted for 3%; Eastern Cape accounted for 2%; and Limpopo accounted for 1% of Sunday’s new cases.  Loading… (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));